9/no-russian-modern-warfare-3-2-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/no-russian-modern-warfare-3-2-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/no-russian-modern-warfare-3-2-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3501963" class="wp-caption-text"> 《使命召唤：现代战争 2》图片来源：动视</figcaption></figure><p>“少数片段描绘了更激烈的暴力行为：恐怖分子占领了一架飞机；恐怖分子（装扮成警察和护理人员）在体育场大厅内射杀逃跑的平民；航空公司乘客在飞机上遭到枪击；囚犯在牢房内被枪杀，”摘要中写道。</p><p> The airplane scene potentially pertains to the post-credits scene of <em>Modern Warfare 2</em> and that it is actually a cutscene lifted from <em>Modern Warfare 3</em> . In the original “No Russian”, the events occur at an airport, but the rating mentioned a “stadium concourse”.</p><p> This could be interpreted to be two different instances where Makarov is able to carry out two attacks – one on the airplane and airport and one in the stadium. Whether the player participates in one or both of them is not clear from the description, however.</p><p> In other gaming news, <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/gaming-news/need-for-speed-developer-will-now-support-the-battlefield-series-3501841">Criterion has been brought on board the support of the Battlefield series</a> , with <a href="https://www.nme.com/brands/electronic-arts">EA</a> Entertainment general manager Vince Zampella praising the developer&#39;s “rich history in gaming”.</p><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/gaming-news/call-of-duty-modern-warfare-3-may-feature-multiple-no-russian-style-missions-3501931">&#39;Call Of Duty: Modern Warfare 3&#39; may feature multiple “No Russian”-style missions</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
